x$ 2.1 kpc\nand a 0.5-10.0 keV X-ray luminosity upper limit of 2.0 $\\times$ 10$^{33}$ erg\ns$^{-1}$. Such an X-ray luminosity is consistent with a white dwarf accretor in\na magnetic cataclysmic variable system. To date, CX19 is only the second\ndeeply-eclipsing intermediate polar with X-ray eclipses and the first which is\noptically accessible.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2016 00:58:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-17"}
